.gitignore for Django Backend
You can use the following .gitignore file for your Django backend project. It's designed to ignore common files and directories that are generated during development and should not be committed to version control.

# Byte-compiled files
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Virtual environment
/venv/
.venv/

# Database files
*.sqlite3
/db.sqlite3

# Media and static files
/media/
/static/

# IDE-specific files
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.bak
.DS_Store

# Django-specific files
/migrations/
/staticfiles/
/local_settings.py
.env